Septic Smart Week is Sept. 14-18, 2020. Are you on septic or sewer? If you don't know, look at
your water bill. Homes with septic tanks do not pay sewer treatment fees. Those on sewer pay
for treatment at one of Cobb's four water reclamation facilities. If you are not paying sewer fees,
then you should be paying a waste hauler to pump your tank and inspect your septic system.
Septic systems require pumping every 3-5 years to remove solids and address concerns. Many
factors impact system effectiveness including volume of water used; number of people in the
home; condition of the drainfield; and presence of tree roots in the pipes, tank, and drainfield. Be
Septic Smart. Maintain your system, attend a free Septic 101 Workshop on 9/25, and learn more
